<TITLE> 4 ACI mugging 'suspects' held </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com)  Detectives have detained four suspects on charge of mugging Tk 52 lakh of ACI company in Tejgaon industrial area, a police officer said on Friday. Police also retrieved Tk 1.3 lakh on their confession, deputy commissioner of Detective Branch of police Mainul Hasan said at a news briefing at the DB headquarters. The arrestees are Hazrat Ali, a driver of ACI, tea stall owner Khokan, Peyar Ali and Illias Hossain known as Sekul. Police claimed Peyar and Sekul were professional muggers. The arrestees are being interrogated in remand. The money was snatched away by muggers on Sunday. Hasan said police identified up to 12 people suspected to have been involved in the incident. bd
